race.comment: Wide open. SHAULA (10) was disappointing on face value last time but did cover ground throughout before fading. Has placed over a mile when trained in Victoria and off the inside draw today is worth another chance. SOCIAL AFFAIR (8) is fitter for two runs back and has upside. Scored her maiden win last time at Bunbury and extra trip looks a plus. Drawn for a nice run. POINT ROCKS (2) is another third-up from a spell. Not far away in a Class 3 last time and although first try at this extra trip has drawn for a good run. ACROSS GENERATIONS (5) was solid fresh over 1300m at Belmont and will be much improved. Can be much closer this time off the good gate. ALMA MATER (6) made good late ground in a run better than it looked last time and can sneak into the frame.
